otal estimated costs',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(17,5,'PHP 50,000',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(18,5,'PHP 62,500',0,'This applies 25% to billed price; the 25% markup is on COST, so GP rate on billed price is 20%',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(19,5,'PHP 200,000',0,'This is the cost portion (80% of billed price), not the unrealized profit',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(20,5,'PHP 37,500',0,'Incorrect calculation; the overvaluation equals the markup portion in ending inventory',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(21,6,'PHP 70,000',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(22,6,'PHP 100,000',0,'Must offset loan payable against capital; loan to partnership REDUCES loss absorption',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(23,6,'PHP 130,000',0,'Loan payable is a DEDUCTION not an addition; it represents amount A owes to partnership',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(24,6,'PHP 30,000',0,'This is only the loan payable; loss absorption = capital minus loan payable',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(25,7,'Legal ownership of more than 50% of shares',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(26,7,'Power over the investee through existing rights',0,'Power is the first element of control under PFRS 10.7',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(27,7,'Exposure or rights to variable returns from involvement',0,'Variable returns is the second element of control under PFRS 10.7',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(28,7,'Ability to use power to affect the amount of returns',0,'Link between power and returns is the third element of control under PFRS 10.7',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(29,8,'PHP 5,450,000',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(30,8,'PHP 5,600,000',0,'This adds share of net income but forgets to deduct share of dividends',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(31,8,'PHP 5,000,000',0,'This is initial cost only; equity method requires adjustment for investor\'s share of earnings',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(32,8,'PHP 5,350,000',0,'Incorrect calculation; must apply 30% to both net income and dividends separately',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(33,9,'Risk assessment process',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(34,9,'Control activities',0,'Control activities are the policies and procedures that help ensure management directives are carried out, not risk identification',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(35,9,'Information and communication',0,'This component deals with identifying, capturing, and exchanging information, not assessing risks',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(36,9,'Monitoring of controls',0,'Monitoring assesses the quality of internal control performance over time, not initial risk identification',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(37,10,'Send positive confirmation requests directly to customers',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(38,10,'Vouch sales invoices to shipping documents',0,'This tests occurrence of sales, not existence of receivables at year-end',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(39,10,'Review subsequent cash receipts in the client\'s records',0,'Internal documents are less reliable than external confirmations for existence',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(40,10,'Perform analytical procedures on accounts receivable aging',0,'Analytical procedures provide circumstantial evidence, not direct evidence of existence',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(41,11,'Unmodified opinion',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(42,11,'Qualified opinion',0,'Qualified opinion is issued when there are material but not pervasive misstatements or scope limitations',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(43,11,'Adverse opinion',0,'Adverse opinion is issued when misstatements are material AND pervasive',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(44,11,'Disclaimer of opinion',0,'Disclaimer is issued when auditor cannot obtain sufficient appropriate audit evidence',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(45,12,'Performance materiality is set lower than overall materiality to reduce the risk that aggregate uncorrected misstatements exceed materiality',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(46,12,'Materiality is a fixed percentage of net income for all entities',0,'Materiality involves professional judgment and varies based on entity circumstances and user needs',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(47,12,'Once set at planning, materiality cannot be revised during the audit',0,'PSA 320.12 requires the auditor to revise materiality if information becomes available that would have caused a different amount',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(48,12,'Performance materiality is always set at 50% of overall materiality',0,'No fixed percentage exists; performance materiality is based on auditor judgment considering assessment of RMM',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(49,13,'Obtain reasonable assurance that financial statements are free from material misstatement due to fraud or error',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(50,13,'Detect all instances of fraud regardless of materiality',0,'Auditors provide reasonable, not absolute assurance; focus is on MATERIAL misstatement',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(51,13,'Prevent and detect fraud through implementation of internal controls',0,'Prevention and detection of fraud is management\'s responsibility, not the auditor\'s',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(52,13,'Guarantee that no fraud exists in the entity\'s financial statements',0,'An audit provides reasonable assurance, not a guarantee; inherent limitations exist',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(53,14,'Those charged with governance',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(54,14,'The external regulatory authority',0,'External reporting may be required, but communication to TCWG should come first under PSA 260',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(55,14,'The company\'s shareholders at the annual meeting',0,'Auditor communicates to TCWG, not directly to shareholders',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(56,14,'Law enforcement agencies',0,'Legal reporting may be required, but professional standards require TCWG communication first',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(57,15,'The inventory includes items requiring subjective valuation estimates',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(58,15,'The entity has a simple, stable inventory system with few product lines',0,'Simple, stable systems with few products suggest LOWER inherent risk',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(59,15,'Inventory turnover is consistent with industry norms',0,'Consistent turnover suggests normal operations and lower inherent risk',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(60,15,'Physical inventory counts are conducted frequently',0,'Frequent counts are a CONTROL that reduces detection risk, not an inherent risk factor',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(61,16,'Include an Emphasis of Matter paragraph without modifying the opinion',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(62,16,'Issue a qualified opinion with explanatory paragraph',0,'Qualified opinion is for material misstatement or scope limitation, not going concern with adequate disclosure',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(63,16,'Issue an adverse opinion due to the going concern uncertainty',0,'Adverse opinion is for material and pervasive misstatement, not for properly disclosed going concern',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(64,16,'Issue a disclaimer of opinion due to uncertainty',0,'Disclaimer is for scope limitations, not for properly disclosed going concern uncertainty',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(65,17,'Apply the change prospectively using the exchange rate at the date of change for all items',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(66,17,'Restate all prior period comparative financial statements retrospectively',0,'PAS 21.35 requires prospective application from the date of change, not retrospective restatement',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(67,17,'Recognize the cumulative translation adjustment immediately in profit or loss',0,'Translation differences remain in equity; they are not recycled to P&L upon functional currency change under PAS 21.37',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(68,17,'Continue using historical rates for all non-monetary items indefinitely',0,'Non-monetary items are translated at the rate on the date of change, which becomes their new deemed cost',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(69,18,'Recognize the difference in other comprehensive income',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(70,18,'Recognize the difference immediately in profit or loss',0,'PFRS 9.5.6.5 specifically requires recognition in OCI for amortized cost to FVOCI reclassifications',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(71,18,'Adjust retained earnings as a prior period adjustment',0,'Reclassifications are applied prospectively from reclassification date, not as prior period adjustments',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(72,18,'No adjustment is required as both categories use the same measurement',0,'Amortized cost and FVOCI use different measurements; fair value adjustment is required upon reclassification',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(73,19,'PHP 2,500,000',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(74,19,'PHP 1,500,000',0,'This ignores accumulated depreciation; you must compare fair value to carrying amount, not original cost',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(75,19,'PHP 2,000,000',0,'Incorrect calculation; the carrying amount after 2 years of depreciation is PHP 9,000,000',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(76,19,'PHP 11,500,000',0,'This is the fair value, not the revaluation surplus; surplus = FV minus carrying amount',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(77,20,'Present obligation from past event, probable outflow of resources, and reliable estimate of the amount',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(78,20,'Future obligation, possible outflow of resources, and reasonable estimate',0,'The obligation must be PRESENT (not future), outflow must be PROBABLE (not possible), and estimate must be RELIABLE',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(79,20,'Present obligation, certain outflow of resources, and exact amount determinable',0,'Certainty is not required; \'probable\' outflow and \'reliable estimate\' (not exact) are the thresholds',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(80,20,'Legal obligation only, probable outflow, and best estimate available',0,'Constructive obligations also qualify; the obligation need not be legal only',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(81,21,'PHP 50,000 (12-month ECL)',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(82,21,'PHP 200,000 (Lifetime ECL)',0,'Lifetime ECL is recognized only when credit risk has SIGNIFICANTLY INCREASED since initial recognition',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(83,21,'PHP 125,000 (Average of 12-month and lifetime)',0,'PFRS 9 uses a staged approach, not averaging; Stage 1 uses 12-month ECL only',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(84,21,'No loss allowance until actual default occurs',0,'PFRS 9 requires forward-looking ECL recognition from Day 1, not incurred loss model',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(85,22,'At the transaction price adjusted for the time value of money, with interest expense or income recognized separately',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(86,22,'At the cash selling price without any adjustment for financing',0,'PFRS 15.60-65 requires adjustment for significant financing component to reflect cash selling price',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(87,22,'At the total amount receivable including all financing charges',0,'This would overstate revenue; financing component must be separated and recognized as interest',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(88,22,'Defer all revenue recognition until cash is fully collected',0,'PFRS 15 requires revenue recognition when performance obligations are satisfied, adjusted for financing',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(89,23,'PHP 1,300,000',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(90,23,'PHP 800,000',0,'This includes only service cost; net interest cost must also be recognized in P&L',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(91,23,'PHP 5,000,000',0,'This is the net defined benefit liability (balance sheet item), not the expense',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(92,23,'PHP 500,000',0,'This includes only net interest; service cost must also be recognized in P&L',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(93,24,'Allocate corporate assets to CGUs on a reasonable and consistent basis, or test impairment at the smallest group of CGUs to which corporate assets can be allocated',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(94,24,'Exclude corporate assets entirely from impairment testing',0,'PAS 36.102 requires corporate assets to be included in impairment testing at some level',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(95,24,'Recognize impairment only if the entire entity shows indicators of impairment',0,'Impairment testing should be done at CGU or group of CGUs level, not only entity-wide',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(96,24,'Test corporate assets separately as individual assets',0,'Corporate assets generally do not generate independent cash flows and cannot be tested individually',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(97,25,'Present value of PHP 1,000,000 for 5 years at 8% discount rate',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(98,25,'PHP 5,000,000 (total undiscounted payments)',0,'PFRS 16 requires present value measurement, not nominal/undiscounted amount',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(99,25,'Fair value of the underlying asset',0,'Fair value is used to determine if rate implicit exists; lease liability uses PV of payments',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(100,25,'Present value using risk-free rate',0,'If implicit rate is not determinable, use incremental borrowing rate, not risk-free rate',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(101,26,'PHP 4,000 Unfavorable total: PHP 21,000 F price variance and PHP 25,000 U quantity variance',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(102,26,'PHP 4,000 Favorable total: PHP 21,000 F price variance and PHP 25,000 F quantity variance',0,'The quantity variance is unfavorable because actual quantity (10,500 kg) exceeded standard quantity (10,000 kg); using 500 kg more than standard at PHP 50 = PHP 25,000 U',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(103,26,'PHP 4,000 Unfavorable total: PHP 20,000 F price variance and PHP 24,000 U quantity variance',0,'Price variance uses actual quantity purchased: (PHP 50 - PHP 48) x 10,500 = PHP 21,000 F, not PHP 20,000',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(104,26,'PHP 46,000 Unfavorable total: PHP 21,000 U price variance and PHP 25,000 U quantity variance',0,'The price variance is favorable because actual price (PHP 48) was less than standard price (PHP 50), not unfavorable',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(105,27,'Profitability Index of 1.08; Accept the project',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(106,27,'Profitability Index of 0.92; Reject the project',0,'This incorrectly divides the initial investment by PV of inflows; PI = PV of inflows / Initial investment, not the inverse',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(107,27,'Profitability Index of 1.50; Accept the project',0,'This uses undiscounted cash flows (PHP 3,000,000 / PHP 2,000,000 = 1.50); PI must use present value of future cash flows',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(108,27,'Profitability Index of 0.80; Reject the project',0,'This calculation error likely used wrong PV factor or divided incorrectly; correct PI is 1.08',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(109,28,'4,000 units (2,400 units of A and 1,600 units of B)',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(110,28,'3,600 units (2,160 units of A and 1,440 units of B)',0,'This used simple average CM of PHP 47.50 instead of weighted-average CM of PHP 45 based on 60:40 sales mix',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(111,28,'5,143 units (3,086 units of A and 2,057 units of B)',0,'This used only Product A\'s lower CM of PHP 35 for entire calculation instead of weighted-average',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(112,28,'3,000 units (1,800 units of A and 1,200 units of B)',0,'This used only Product B\'s higher CM of PHP 60 for entire calculation instead of weighted-average',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(113,29,'PHP 42,000 less under traditional costing',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(114,29,'PHP 42,000 more under traditional costing',0,'Traditional costing assigns Product X only PHP 48,000 (20% of overhead) while ABC assigns PHP 90,000 (37.5%); X receives LESS, not more, under traditional',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(115,29,'PHP 90,000 less under traditional costing',0,'PHP 90,000 is the total ABC allocation to Product X, not the difference between the two methods',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(116,29,'PHP 48,000 less under traditional costing',0,'PHP 48,000 is the traditional costing allocation to Product X, not the difference; the difference is PHP 90,000 - PHP 48,000 = PHP 42,000',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(117,30,'PHP 320,000',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(118,30,'PHP 300,000',0,'This uses an incorrect variable cost rate or fixed cost calculation; the correct rate is PHP 30/MH with fixed costs of PHP 140,000',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(119,30,'PHP 305,000',0,'This likely used average cost per unit (PHP 305,000/6,000) instead of separating fixed and variable components using high-low method',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(120,30,'PHP 340,000',0,'This calculation error may have used wrong activity levels or cost figures in the high-low formula',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(121,31,'Make internally; saves PHP 10,000 annually',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(122,31,'Buy externally; saves PHP 50,000 annually',0,'This incorrectly compared full absorption cost (PHP 70) to buy price, ignoring that 40% of fixed OH (PHP 8) is unavoidable and continues regardless',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(123,31,'Make internally; saves PHP 200,000 annually',0,'This incorrectly treated all fixed overhead (PHP 20) as avoidable; only 60% (PHP 12) is eliminable, not the full amount',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(124,31,'Buy externally; saves PHP 70,000 annually',0,'This likely used variable costs only (PHP 50) for make vs PHP 55 buy, ignoring avoidable fixed costs of PHP 12/unit',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(125,32,'80% increase due to operating leverage of 4.0',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(126,32,'20% increase proportional to sales increase',0,'Operating income does not increase proportionally with sales due to operating leverage; fixed costs remain constant, amplifying profit changes',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(127,32,'40% increase due to operating leverage of 2.0',0,'Operating leverage = CM/Operating Income = PHP 2,000,000/PHP 500,000 = 4.0, not 2.0',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(128,32,'60% increase due to operating leverage of 3.0',0,'The degree of operating leverage is CM (PHP 2,000,000) divided by Operating Income (PHP 500,000) = 4.0, not 3.0',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(129,33,'Replace; net advantage of PHP 50,000 over 5 years',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(130,33,'Keep old; replacing causes PHP 50,000 loss from book value write-off',0,'The PHP 50,000 loss on disposal (PHP 100,000 BV - PHP 50,000 sale) is a sunk cost; book value is irrelevant for future decisions',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(131,33,'Replace; net advantage of PHP 250,000 over 5 years',0,'This counted only operating savings (PHP 250,000) without deducting net equipment cost (PHP 200,000)',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(132,33,'Keep old; new equipment costs PHP 250,000 net',0,'Net equipment cost is PHP 200,000 (PHP 300,000 - PHP 50,000 trade - PHP 50,000 salvage), not PHP 250,000; and this ignores operating savings',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(133,34,'Z acquires valid ownership under the doctrine of seller in possession',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(134,34,'Z acquires no ownership because Y had no title to transfer',0,'While Y technically lacked full ownership, the Civil Code protects innocent purchasers when the seller is in possession with owner\'s consent',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(135,34,'Z acquires voidable ownership subject to X\'s right of rescission',0,'Z\'s ownership is not voidable; as innocent purchaser for value from seller in possession, Z acquires absolute ownership',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(136,34,'Z acquires ownership only upon X receiving full payment from Y',0,'Z\'s ownership is independent of Y\'s payment to X; Z\'s protection as innocent purchaser is immediate and unconditional',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(137,35,'No, H as holder in due course of a bearer instrument takes free of P\'s claim',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(138,35,'Yes, because theft is a real defense available against all holders',0,'Theft is a personal defense, not a real defense; HDC takes free of personal defenses including theft from prior holder',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(139,35,'Yes, because a stolen instrument cannot be negotiated',0,'Bearer instruments can be negotiated by mere delivery; even a thief can negotiate to an HDC who takes good title',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(140,35,'No, but only if H can prove ignorance of the theft',0,'HDC status is determined at time of taking; once established, the burden is not ongoing proof of ignorance',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(141,36,'PHP 150,000 (C\'s share plus half of B\'s share)',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(142,36,'PHP 100,000 (C\'s share only)',0,'Under Article 1217, when a co-debtor is insolvent, the debtor paying must share the loss with the other solvent co-debtors proportionately',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(143,36,'PHP 200,000 (C\'s share plus entire B\'s share)',0,'The insolvent\'s share is divided among ALL solvent debtors (A and C equally), not charged entirely to C',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(144,36,'PHP 300,000 (total amount paid)',0,'A can only seek reimbursement for co-debtors\' shares; A must bear his own share plus portion of insolvent\'s share',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(145,37,'Issued shares increase to 66,000; no change in total stockholders\' equity',1,NULL,1,1,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(146,37,'Issued shares increase to 66,000; total stockholders\' equity increases by PHP 600,000',0,'Stock dividends do not increase total equity; they merely transfer from retained earnings to capital stock (equity reclassification)',1,2,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(147,37,'Authorized shares must first be increased before stock dividends can be declared',0,'There are 40,000 unissued shares available (100,000 - 60,000); 6,000 new shares needed for 10% dividend can be issued',1,3,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(148,37,'Issued shares increase to 70,000; retained earnings decrease by PHP 1,000,000',0,'10% of 60,000 shares = 6,000 new shares (not 10,000); RE decreases by 6,000 x PHP 100 = PHP 600,000',1,4,'2026-01-22 22:36:11'),(149,38,'